# Fallow Quality Audits

Run [Fallow](https://docs.fallow.tools) before merging significant work. Static analysis is free; use it as the quality gate.

## When to run

| Trigger | Command |
|---|---|
| **Before merge / after coding** | `fallow dupes --format json --quiet \|\| true` |
| Before PR / commit | `fallow audit --base main --format json --quiet \|\| true` |
| Changed files only | `fallow dead-code --changed-since main --format json --quiet \|\| true` |

Post-coding: duplication eliminated and dead code removed are **required deliverables** per AFDP (`docs/architecture-first-development.md`).

Always append `|| true` — exit 1 means issues found, not crash.

## Fix before merge

- **Duplicate code clones** — extract shared module to `packages/shared` or `components/ui`
- **Unused exports/files** — remove or `fallow fix --dry-run` then `--yes`
- **Boundary violations** — respect monorepo zones (see `.fallowrc.json`)
- **Complexity hotspots** — split functions > cyclomatic 15 before adding features

## Agent workflow

1. `fallow dupes --format json --quiet || true` — zero tolerance for copy-paste components
2. `fallow audit --base main --gate new-only --format json --quiet || true` — no new dead code in PR
3. Consolidate duplicates before creating a third similar file

## Suppression

Use sparingly: `// fallow-ignore-next-line` with a reason comment. Prefer fixing the root cause.
